  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposed rear dormer would be visually obtrusive, would not respect the established roof form of the subject property, and would be harmful to the character of the subject dwelling and the local area, which is substantiated by the need for the proposed dormer to cut into the roof of the existing two storey projected element, contrary to the high quality design aspirations of the National Planning Policy Framework (2019), policy D3 D(11) of the London Plan (2021), policy CS1. B Core Strategy (2012); policy DM1 of Harrow Development Management Local Plan Policies (2013), and the Supplementary Planning Document: Residential Design Guide (2010).",
    "Reason : 2 - Notwithstanding reason No. 1, in the absence of sectional drawings, it has not been demonstrated that the floor to ceiling heights would be acceptable and that the proposal would not create a poor standard of living accommodation for  the potential future occupiers, to the detriment of their residential amenity, contrary to the National Planning Policy Framework (2019), Policy D6 of The London Plan (2021), Policies DM 1 and DM 26 of the Harrow Development Management Policies Local Plan (2013), the Mayor of London Supplementary Planning Guidance Housing (2016),  and the adopted Supplementary Planning Document: Residential Design Guide   (2010)."
